# MongoDB Setup

This example will be hosted on MongoDB Atlas

1. Naviate to the Google Cloud [website](https://console.cloud.google.com/) and login

2. Click on `Select a project` in the nagivation bar, then `New Project`

3. Give your project a name, then click `Create`

4. Once the project is created, make sure it is selected in the navigation bar, then select `APIs & Services` > `Credentials`

5. Click on `Configure Consent Screen`, select the `External` option, then `Create`

6. Then, enter an app name, a user support email, and a developer contact email, then click `Save and Continue`

7. Click `Save and Continue` two more times, then `Back to Dashboard`

8. Now, head to the `Credentials` page on the sidebar, then click `Create Credentials` > `OAuth Client ID`

9. Set the application type to `web application` and give it a name

10. Under `Authorized JavaScript Origins`, add two URLs:

    - `http://localhost`
    - `http://localhost:3000`

11. Under `Authorized Redirect URIs`, add the two same URLs:

    - `http://localhost`
    - `http://localhost:3000`

12. Now click `Create` to generate your client ID and copy it

13. Paste the connection string in the `.env` file in our `client` folder

```diff
- REACT_APP_GOOGLE_API_TOKEN = ""
+ REACT_APP_GOOGLE_API_TOKEN = "<...>.apps.googleusercontent.com"
```

14. Now, edit `App.tsx` to include this new ID:

```diff
    <BrowserRouter>
-     <GoogleOAuthProvider clientId="">
+     <GoogleOAuthProvider
+       clientId={`${process.env.REACT_APP_GOOGLE_API_TOKEN}`}
+     >
        <h1>App</h1>
      </GoogleOAuthProvider>
    </BrowserRouter>
```
